# ========================================
# Commit Message Format
# ========================================
#
#   Emoji  scope : summary
#     │      │       │
#     │      │       └─⫸ Brief summary in present tense
#     │      │
#     │      └─⫸ Affected area, package, file, etc.
#     │
#     └─⫸ Commit type emoji
#
#
# ====================================
# Commit Type Emojis
# ====================================
#
# ✨  New features
#      e.g. add image paste support, add settings page, add new command
#
# 🐛  Bug fixes
#      e.g. fix crashes, fix incorrect conversions, add exception handling
#
# ♻️  Code refactoring without feature additions or bug fixes
#      e.g. split large functions, reorganize classes, remove duplicate code
#
# 🏗️  Add, remove, or modify external dependencies and build settings
#      e.g. update package.json, add npm packages, add eslint.config.js
#
# 🔄  Continuous Integration (CI) related changes
#      e.g. update GitHub Actions, add automated tests, configure automated releases
#
# 📚  Documentation changes
#      e.g. add installation instructions, add usage examples, update screenshots
#
# 🛠️  Performance improvements
#      e.g. reduce unnecessary recalculations, speed up searches, reduce memory usage
#
# 🧹  Maintenance and miscellaneous tasks
#      e.g. update .gitignore, run npm update, update licenses, reorganize folders
#
# 🧪  Add or modify tests
#      e.g. add unit tests, update test cases, modify test environment configuration
#
# 🎨  Code style and formatting changes (no functional impact)
#      e.g. run Prettier, fix indentation, clean up line breaks
#
#
# ========================================
# Commit Body
# ========================================
#
# Use bullet points (*) to explain changes and motivations.
# You may compare previous and new behavior to clarify impact.
#
#
# ========================================
# Example
# ========================================
#
# ✨ extension : add clipboard image support
#
# * Add image paste support from clipboard
# * Save pasted images to workspace
# * Insert generated Markdown automatically
